    "text": " 12 AM / Updated 19 minutes ago Melrose offers to buy Britain's GKN for $10.2 bln Reuters Staff 1 Min Read \nJan 17 (Reuters) - Turnaround specialists Melrose on Wednesday made a firm offer to buy GKN for 430.1 pence per share or 7.4 billion pounds ($10.18 billion) after meeting its shareholders, adding pressure on the British engineering company to accept the deal. \nGKN was under pressure from U.S. activist investor Elliott Advisors to open talks with Melrose having rebuffed a 405 pence per share cash-and-stock offer this month. $1 = 0.7269 pounds Reporting by Noor Zainab Hussain in Bengaluru; editing by Jason Neely",
